ration, Lamrani shows how the media systematically shapes our understanding of Cuban reality. This book, provides an alternative view, combining a scholar's eye for complexity with a journalist's hunger for the facts"--cProvided by publisher.  a4300aPaís (Madrid, Spain) 0aSpanish newspapersxObjectivity. 0aJournalismxObjectivityzSpain. 0aCubaxPress coveragezSpain.1 aOberg, Larry R.,etranslator.  aPN 5319 M33 P355 2015hUAHS-Bi0162035242245  aPN 5319 M33 P355 2015wLCc1i0162035242245d3/15/2015e3/8/2015lON_SHELFmUAHSSn2p$150.00rYsYtBOOKu2/26/201501ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n82236348bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/212459381